Credit Card Fraud Detection using Machine Learning
1. Introduction

Fraud detection is one of the most important applications of Machine Learning in the financial sector. The objective of this project is to build a classification model capable of identifying fraudulent credit card transactions.

2. Dataset Description

The dataset contains credit card transactions with 31 columns:

Time
V1 to V28
Amount
Class

The target variable is:

Class = 0 (Normal)
Class = 1 (Fraud)

The dataset is highly imbalanced because fraudulent transactions represent only a small fraction of all transactions.

3. Data Cleaning

The following preprocessing steps were performed:

Checked for missing values.
Removed duplicate records.
Verified dataset consistency.

No missing values were found in the dataset.

4. Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

EDA was performed to understand:

Class distribution.
Feature relationships.
Correlation matrix.

The analysis revealed a severe class imbalance.

5. Data Preprocessing

The following preprocessing steps were applied:

Feature scaling using StandardScaler.
Train-test split (80%-20%).
SMOTE for balancing the minority class.
6. Machine Learning Models

Two models were trained:

Logistic Regression

A baseline linear classification model.

Random Forest

An ensemble learning model capable of capturing complex patterns.

Hyperparameter tuning was performed using GridSearchCV.

7. Evaluation Metrics

The following metrics were used:

Precision
Recall
ROC-AUC Score
Confusion Matrix

Accuracy was avoided because the dataset is highly imbalanced.

8. Results
Model	Precision	Recall	ROC-AUC
Logistic Regression	0.053	0.874	0.963
Random Forest	0.911	0.758	0.973

The Random Forest model achieved superior performance.

9. Conclusion

This project successfully developed a fraud detection system using Machine Learning techniques.

The Random Forest model was selected as the best-performing model due to its high precision and excellent ROC-AUC score.

Future improvements may include:

Deep Learning approaches
Real-time fraud detection systems
Feature engineering enhancements